The legal basis for the processing is Art. 6 (1) f) General Data Protection Regulation.
Cookies are small text files, which can be stored on your computer.
They have the purpose to store data. We need basically your consent to use cookies.
In regard to cookies that are strictly necessary to provide these webpages a consent of the user is not required.
You can decide yourself whether and to what extent you want accept the use of cookies with the aid of your browser settings.
At the same place you can erase cookies, which are already stored on your computer.
At Firefox you can find cookie settings in the menu Extras->Options->Data Protection.

This website uses Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google, Inc. ("Google").
Google Analytics uses "cookies"(see above). The information generated by the cookies about your use of the website will be transmitted to and stored by Google on servers in the United States.
Within the territory of the Member States of the European Union and other parties to the Agreement on the European Economic Area Google truncates/anonymizes the last octet of the IP address.
Only in exceptional cases, the full IP address is sent to and shortened by Google servers in the USA.
The IP address transmitted by your browser within the frame of Google Analytics will not be associated with any other data held by Google.
We use Google Analytics to evaluate the use of our website and to improve our web services on the basis of the statistics provided by Google Analytics.
The legal basis for the processing is Art. 6 (1) f) General Data Protection Regulation.
